"{\"uid\": \"rte.ie-brainstorm-2024-0805-1463551-paris-olympics-2024-host-city-costs-economics\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Analysis: Few cities can now afford to host the Olympics, but Paris may win gold by smart use of existing facilities and low-cost temporary venues  BySid PanayiandBorja Garc\\u00eda,Loughborough University  Many of the world's best athletes are currently competing in the firstOlympic Gamesto be held inParissince1924.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 62, \"end\": 67, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7634271795306875e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French capital is buoyant with excitement and its local businesses filled with paying tourists from all over the world.\", \"from\": 313, \"to\": 436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9668283456444523, \"rank\": 0.02715079905292996, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, it's difficult not to be tempted into booking a weekend getaway to see the spectacle up close.\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 539, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But are the Olympics really a good deal for host cities?\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 597, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The evidencesuggestsa resounding no.\", \"from\": 598, \"to\": 634, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Host cities almost always blow their budget on the Games, having to invest heavily in specific sporting facilities, as well as accommodation and transportation for the influx of athletes and tourists.\", \"from\": 635, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The delayedTokyo Gamesin 2021, for example, ended up costing anestimated $15.4 billion, exceeding the proposed budget by 244%.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 963, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And it was a similar story four years before - theRio Olympicscost 352% morethan the initial proposal.\", \"from\": 964, \"to\": 1066, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From IOC Media in 2017, the winning Paris presentation for the 2024 Olympics bid  As part of the bidding process to stage the Games, potential host cities and governments are required toguaranteethat they will cover these costly overruns.\", \"from\": 1070, \"to\": 1308, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1106, \"end\": 1111, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7634271795306875e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given the financial drain a home Olympics so often proves to be, it is no surprise that there has been a steady decline in the number of formal bids to host the Games over the past decade.\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A total of11 citiessubmitted applications to host the2004 Athens Olympics, followed by10 bidsforBeijingin 2008 andnineforLondonin 2012.\", \"from\": 1499, \"to\": 1634, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1557, \"end\": 1563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"score\": 0.9999891314450366, \"rank\": 1.0849565623164743e-05, \"text\": \"Athens\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After London there was a significant reduction.\", \"from\": 1635, \"to\": 1682, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1635, \"end\": 1647, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"After London\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Richard_Jefferies\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 2016 Olympics was awarded toRiofrom justfour bids, 2020 went to Tokyo fromthreeand there were onlytwo bidssubmitted by cities wanting to host the 2024 Games.\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1844, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.536290701571222e-23, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This declining interest prompted the International Olympic Committee (IOC) to award the2028 Olympicsto Los Angeles, the only other bidder for the 2024 Games, without undertaking a public bidding process.\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 2048, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1882, \"end\": 1919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee (IOC)\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1948, \"end\": 1959, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999409128595, \"rank\": 5.900432619002022e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reduced interest in hosting the Games has been influenced in large part by negative public opinion.\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2153, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The cost of the 2004 Olympics, for example, wasthought by manyto have triggered Greece's financial crisis.\", \"from\": 2154, \"to\": 2260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2234, \"end\": 2240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_government-debt_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.1292524393712185e-12, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_government-debt_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_government-debt_crisis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Within days of the closing ceremony, Greecewarnedthe euro area that its public debt and deficit figures would be worse than expected.\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2394, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It subsequently posted a deficit more than double the eurozone limit and years ofeconomic hardshipfollowed.\", \"from\": 2395, \"to\": 2502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 400,000 people emigrated and the unemployment rate for people aged under 25 had reached 58% by 2013.\", \"from\": 2503, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"From Sideprojects, what happened in Greece after the 2004 Olympics  There is also a feeling among the public that the cost of hosting the Olympics will ultimately land at the feet of the taxpayer.\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2813, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2653, \"end\": 2659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_government-debt_crisis\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.1292524393712185e-12, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_government-debt_crisis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_government-debt_crisis\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Montreal hosted the Games in1976and a mammoth $1.1 billion was spent on a new Olympic stadium alone, famously needed decades topay off its debt.\", \"from\": 2814, \"to\": 2958, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2814, \"end\": 2822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7290565848872588e-15, \"text\": \"Montreal\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Montreal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fear of the massive costs involved led bothBostonandBudapestto withdraw their bids to host the 2024 Olympic Games, citing a lack of public support and strong political objections.\", \"from\": 2960, \"to\": 3139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2015 the then mayor of Boston, Martin Walsh, said hosting the Games was \\\"a commitment that I can not make without ensuring the city and its residents will be protected.\\\"\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3312, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3166, \"end\": 3172, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"score\": 0.9999999999872671, \"rank\": 1.2609070249492014e-11, \"text\": \"Boston\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boston\"}, {\"begin\": 3174, \"end\": 3180, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"score\": 0.9999857523513119, \"rank\": 1.3977351230308176e-05, \"text\": \"Martin\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glenn_L._Martin_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He added: \\\"I refuse to mortgage the future of the city away.\\\"\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3374, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In Budapest, more than 250,000 peoplesigned a petition demandingthat the city drop its bid and direct the money towards building modern hospitals and well-equipped schools.\", \"from\": 3375, \"to\": 3547, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3378, \"end\": 3386, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.80656325702118e-16, \"text\": \"Budapest\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Budapest\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Games are not always accompanied by a bleak legacy.\", \"from\": 3549, \"to\": 3608, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1984, the Los Angeles Olympics was held using almost entirely preexisting infrastructure.\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3701, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3622, \"end\": 3642, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999966927071121, \"rank\": 3.3073040012876622e-06, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1984_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That year, the Games turned aUS$215 million profit.\", \"from\": 3702, \"to\": 3753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need your consent to load this rte-player contentWe use rte-player to manage extra content that can set cookies on your device and collect data about your activity.\", \"from\": 3755, \"to\": 3922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please review their details and accept them to load the content.Manage Preferences  From RT\\u00c9 Archives, Jimmy Magee's commentary on John Treacy's silver medal win in the 1984 Los Angeles Olympics  There are reasons to believe Paris could follow suit.\", \"from\": 3923, \"to\": 4172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4012, \"end\": 4015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 4026, \"end\": 4037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Magee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jimmy Magee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Magee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jimmy_Magee\"}, {\"begin\": 4054, \"end\": 4065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Treacy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"John Treacy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Treacy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Treacy\"}, {\"begin\": 4148, \"end\": 4153, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7634271795306875e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The organisers have as far as possible made use ofexisting facilitiesand low-cost temporary venues.\", \"from\": 4173, \"to\": 4272, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This includes a stadium in theshadow of the Eiffel Toweron the Champ de Mars that will host the beach volleyball.\", \"from\": 4273, \"to\": 4386, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So far, the cost of Games looks to havestayed closeto the original budget of US$8.5 billion.\", \"from\": 4387, \"to\": 4479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hosting the Games can also provide lasting benefits for local communities to inherit, regardless of the cost.\", \"from\": 4481, \"to\": 4590, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The London 2012 Olympics, for example, provided new facilities, housing and transports links that have contributed to the regeneration of the city's eastern boroughs.\", \"from\": 4591, \"to\": 4757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4595, \"end\": 4615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.6419207905852e-24, \"text\": \"London 2012 Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a poll conducted ten years after the Games, two-thirds of London adultsagreedthat hosting the Olympics had left a positive legacy.\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4819, \"end\": 4825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999731858686393, \"rank\": 2.615953043685203e-05, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has now reformed its host bidding process by creating a less public campaign for prospective host cities.\", \"from\": 4893, \"to\": 5006, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4897, \"end\": 4900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6046180197806674e-34, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2021, Brisbane won theright to host the 2032 Gameshaving been the first city to go through this new process.\", \"from\": 5007, \"to\": 5118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5016, \"end\": 5024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"score\": 0.9999999996052793, \"rank\": 3.948571884129325e-10, \"text\": \"Brisbane\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brisbane\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rationale behind this change was to stop cities trying to outbid each other competitively, which has previously caused excessive expenditure.\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5264, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is hope this will eventually improve the damaged public perception of hosting the Games.\", \"from\": 5265, \"to\": 5359, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympics is an event steeped in historical importance formed to promote talent excellence, respect and friendship - not to drive economic gain to a city directly  Rather than the city having toadapt to the Games, the IOC has highlighted that there will be a greater emphasis on the games adapting to the city in the future.\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5688, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5582, \"end\": 5585, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6046180197806674e-34, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The plan for Los Angeles in 2028 is forevery venueto either exist already or be temporary, which should have a dramatic effect on expenditure.\", \"from\": 5689, \"to\": 5831, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5702, \"end\": 5713, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999409128595, \"rank\": 5.900432619002022e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This increased flexibility allows governments to discuss the feasibility of hosting with the IOC without having to propose excessive and expensive changes to their cities.\", \"from\": 5832, \"to\": 6003, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5925, \"end\": 5928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6046180197806674e-34, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some feel these changes are not enough.\", \"from\": 6005, \"to\": 6044, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is abeliefamong economists that low and middle-income countries should spare themselves the potential burden, and wealthier countries who can better absorb the costs should be the only viable hosts.\", \"from\": 6045, \"to\": 6249, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"However, it's important to remember that the Olympics has never been a cash machine.\", \"from\": 6251, \"to\": 6335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is an event steeped in historical importance formed to promote talent excellence, respect and friendship - not to drive economic gain to a city directly.\", \"from\": 6336, \"to\": 6492, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sid Panayiis a PhD Candidate in Sport Business atLoughborough University,Borja Garc\\u00edais a Reader in Sport Policy and Governance atLoughborough University.\", \"from\": 6494, \"to\": 6648, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6567, \"end\": 6572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Borgia\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.382089040836986e-29, \"text\": \"Borja\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Borgia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/House_of_Borgia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This article was originally published byThe Conversation.\", \"from\": 6649, \"to\": 6706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The views expressed here are those of the author and do not represent or reflect the views of RT\\u00c9      \\u00a9 RT\\u00c9 2026.\", \"from\": 6708, \"to\": 6822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9.ie is the website of Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann, Ireland's National Public Service Media.\", \"from\": 6823, \"to\": 6913, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6848, \"end\": 6871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9993664851270567, \"rank\": 0.0006339164685885233, \"text\": \"Raidi\\u00f3 Teilif\\u00eds \\u00c9ireann\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}, {\"begin\": 6873, \"end\": 6880, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999994479367, \"rank\": 5.519334883995549e-10, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RT\\u00c9 is not responsible for the content of external internet sites.\", \"from\": 6914, \"to\": 6980, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6914, \"end\": 6917, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"score\": 0.9835396432123026, \"rank\": 0.013767790549921992, \"text\": \"RT\\u00c9\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Raidi\\u00f3_Teilif\\u00eds_\\u00c9ireann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Images Courtesy of Getty Images.\", \"from\": 6982, \"to\": 7014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7001, \"end\": 7006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9999500774630904, \"rank\": 4.976941444902858e-05, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}]}"